Let us examine the vacuum physics. In each ground state, supersymmetry is unbroken and 
the theory is in a Higgs phase. Together with the broken  gauge symmetry, the 
theory also exhibits an unbroken  flavour symmetry, acting on the  and 
. All three vacua have a mass gap, with the 
lightest excitations depending on the ratio 
